In the annual report, Israel showed a strong positive growth in its Jewish population, with stable or declining figures elsewhere. The Jewish demographic increased by 92,400 people since 2019’s revised count, largely due to the country’s gains, the study states. Most of the world’s Jewish population is located in Israel (46 per cent) and the United States (39 per cent).
International data from countries of immigration revealed that Canada is one of the few countries where the Jewish population has been slowly increasing, mostly in the Greater Toronto Area, including newcomers from “Russia, Israel and Iran,” DellaPergola added. There are an estimated 400,000 Jews in Canada, the fourth highest concentration in the world, the report found.
