Unlike a census, the Pew data is not compulsory, said DellaPergola, adding “it’s sort of based on a relatively small sample and so there are all sorts of technical problems and sampling errors,” making the Canadian census data more reliable.
By far, the biggest population growth of Jews occurred in Israel, which at three per cent has the highest birth rate among developed nations. Its ‘law of return’ allows people of Jewish descent to immigrate there and contributed to Israel’s two per cent growth rate in the general population.
Despite those gains, Israel’s Jewish population is growing at a rate that’s two thirds of the general world population. Reaching the numbers prior to the catastrophic losses arising from the Holocaust “may take decades,” the report found.
